A+B+C=\pi
\sin^2A+\sin^2B+\sin^2C=2-2\cos A\cos B\cos C
\sin^2A+\sin^2B+\sin^2C=1-\cos^2C+1-(\cos^2A-\sin^2B)
\displaystyle\cos^2A-\sin^2B=\cos(A+B)\cos(A-B)=\cos(\pi-C)\cos(A-B)
=-\cos C\cos(A-B)
\displaystyle\cos^2C+\cos^2A-\sin^2B=\cos^2C-\cos C\cos(A-B)
\displaystyle=\cos C[\cos C-\cos(A-B)]
\displaystyle=\cos C[-\cos(A+B)-\cos(A-B)]
A+B=\pi-C
