A+B+C = \pi \implies A + B = \pi - C \implies \sin(A+B)=\sin(C) \land \cos(A+B)=-\cos(C)
\sin^2(A) + \sin^2(B) + \sin^2(C) \\ = \sin^2(A) + 1-\cos^2(B) + 1 âˆ’ \cos^2(A+B) \\ =2+(\sin^2(A)-\cos^2(B))-\cos^2(A+B) \\ = 2+\cos(B-A)\cos(A+B)-\cos(A+B)\cos(A+B) \\ = 2+(\cos(B-A)+\cos(A+B))\cos(A+B) \\ = 2 - 2\cos(A)\cos(B)\cos(C)
